        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 2:24PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pinola, or near Mendenhall, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mendenhall and D'Lo around 230 PM CDT.
Sanatorium around 240 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
